This paper discusses the performance of MIMO millimeter wave systems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the impact of hardware impairments, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on beamforming, which is a key aspect of millimeter wave systems and falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
